opean Stability Initiative (a public policy think tank), the Yale-Soros Civic Education Project in Bulgaria, and the Robert Schuman Centre in Florence. Dr. Brand holds a doctoral 306 Short Biographical Summaries of the Authors degree in international and constitutional law from the University of Vienna (2002), where he also obtained his Masters degree in law earlier (1994). His dissertation deals with the development of constitutionalism and human rights protection in UN-administered Kosovo. He also holds degrees from the European University Institute (EUI) in Florence (LL.M., 1997) and from the Johns Hopkins University School of Advanced International Studies (SAIS) in Bologna (1995). R. Sudarshan began working for UNDP in 1991, when he joined the UNDP-India Office as Senior Economist and Assistant Resident Representative, heading the Public Policy Division, and subsequently, also the Human Development Research Centre in New Delhi. In 2000 he joined UNDP-Indonesia as Senior Governance Advisor, and played a role in the establishment of the Partnership for Governance Reform in Indonesia. He was appointed Justice Advisor in 2002 at the UNDP Oslo Governance Centre. In 2005 he was appointed as Policy Advisor, Human Rights, Legal Reforms and Justice Advisor at the UNDP Asia-Pacific Regional Centre in Bangkok. Before joining UNDP, he worked seven years with the Ford Foundation\u2019s South Asia Office in New Delhi, where he was responsible for developing programmes in human rights, social justice, governance, and promotion of private philanthropy. R. Sudarshan was trained in economics at the universities of Bangalore and Delhi (Delhi School of Economics), where he obtained B.A. Hons and M.A. degrees, respectively. He also has a Master\u2019s degree in Politics from Oxford University, where he was a Rhodes Scholar at Balliol College. He was a research fellow at St. John\u2019s College, Cambridge, from 1977 until 1983, where he conducted research and published articles on the interface of law and economics and on judicial review of economic legislation. He has a number of publications on constitutional law, human development, and democratic governance to his credit. In August 2012, Sudarshan will return to academia to join Jindal Global University as Professor and Dean of the Jindal School of Government and Public Policy and concurrently serve as the Executive Director of the Centre for the Study of Poverty and Inequality. Copy Editor Everett Berg holds two bachelor\u2019s degrees and a Master\u2019s degree in Public Administration (MPA) from the Johnson Shoyama Graduate School of Public Policy in Saskatchewan, Canada. He is a trained educator who is working with UNDP on the Legal Empowerment of the Poor initiative at the Asia Pacific Regional Center (APRC) in Bangkok, Thailand.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "a4831a30-4160-45ad-a0d4-4a2a55be7c07": {"__data__": {"id_": "a4831a30-4160-45ad-a0d4-4a2a55be7c07", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/accelerating-achievement-mdgs-ways-and-means-economic-and-social-rights", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Accelerating Achievement of MDGs by Ways and Means of Economic and Social Rights", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/accelerating-achievement-mdgs-ways-and-means-economic-and-social-rights", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "63ca939e4e4157b66a31fca4465909a178a889ad31e9abeb6d177a905e6added"}, "2": {"node_id": "1bf64411-d37c-428f-81a1-ae6d366c8